snippet: By Wednesday evening, police detectives were questioning someone in connection with the shooting of Brandon Lincoln Woodard, which occurred on West 58th Street.
abstract: Investigators searching for gunman who carried out brazen murder of Los Angeles club promoter Brandon Lincoln Woodard on Midtown Manhattan street find getaway car and are processing it for evidence; video-surveillance tape suggests that shooting was done by professionals and that Woodard may have been lured to spot where he was killed.

byline.original: By WENDY RUDERMAN and J. DAVID GOODMAN
byline.contributor: Joseph Goldstein and William K. Rashbaum contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: By Wednesday evening, police detectives were questioning someone in connection with the shooting of Brandon Lincoln Woodard, which occurred on West 58th Street.

headline.seo: Search for Gunman in Midtown Murder Focuses on Queens
headline.main: Hunt for Midtown Killer Focuses on Queens After Getaway Car, a Rental, Is Found
headline.print_headline: Hunt for Midtown Killer Focuses on Queens After Getaway Car, a Rental, Is Found
